Data: Starc to Roy, no run back of a length, pushed across Roy who leaves it alone...doubt we'll see many of them
Starc to Roy, 2 runs similar line and length, this time Roy cuts it behind point and wide of third man to get off the mark
Starc to Roy, 1 wide some swing there, but started on the wrong line and slipped down the leg side
Starc to Roy, 1 wide now that's flung very wide outside off, almost misses the cut strip

Starc to Roy, 2 runs gets back around off stump, but that's a lovely piece of timing by Roy as he pushes forward and places it square through the covers...Warner chases it down well with a flick back just before the rope
Starc to Roy, no run full outside off, 89mph, through to the keeper
Starc to Roy, 1 wide another one down the leg side, Starc's radar isn't in sync yet. Long over to start with
Starc to Roy, no run spears into the pads, a strangled appeal for lbw but that pitched outside leg stump...did Roy a little for pace, though
Starc to Roy, no run a wild swing and a miss to a length ball outside off...a lengthy, wayward over so costing seven isn't too bad a result for Australia
Coulter-Nile to Hales, 1 run on a length, angled into the pads, tucked out to deep square leg
Coulter-Nile to Roy, no run short delivery, around middle and off, but not a full on bouncer...Roy is through his pull shot early and takes it in the stomach
Coulter-Nile to Roy, 1 run uses his feet then swings through the line of a full delivery, skews off a thick outside edge and carries towards third man but lands in front of the fielder
Coulter-Nile to Hales, no run full at off stump, 86mph, defended to the leg side
Coulter-Nile to Hales, 1 run works with the angle coming into him, flicked into square leg
Coulter-Nile to Roy, 1 run well bowled, a length ball nipping into him which he drops towards mid-on for a quick single
Starc to Roy, no run heaves a length delivery into the leg side but picks out the man in front of square
Starc to Roy, no run fuller this time, at the stumps, 90mph, driven into the leg side
Starc to Roy, no run full outside off, Roy was giving himself some room to leg so had to stretch for the delivery and couldn't make contact
Starc to Roy, FOUR runs lovely stroke, a whip-pull by Roy as Starc drops short...placement was the key as he slotted it wide of the man at deep square
Starc to Roy, 1 run back to a full length and it's forced with a straight bat through midwicket but a strong throw from Stoinis keeps them to a single
Starc to Hales, 1 run full at middle and off, 90mph, drop and run into the off side...a smart way to score off the good balls
Cummins to Hales, no run appeal for lbw, a full ball spearing into the pads but that appeared to he shading down the leg side as Hales misses his whip to the leg side
Cummins to Hales, no run another big appeal! A full toss this time. Michael Gough shakes his head again. That looked a bit closer. Replays show it was missing leg.
Cummins to Hales, OUT well, that's done it! 91mph, Hales done for pace. Another low full toss, Hales is late on the stroke, gets an inside edge onto the pads then into the stumps
Cummins to Ali, 1 run yorker-length outside off, 93mph, that's some heat, and Moeen jabs it down to third man off the toe of the bat
Cummins to Roy, no run confident drive from Roy as he strides forward to a full ball on off stump but picks out cover

Cummins to Roy, OUT and another! Two in the over for Cummins. Roy tries to launch a length delivery over the off side, but gets more elevation that distance...still, took a very good catch by Coulter-Nile as he back-tracked from mid-off
Coulter-Nile to Morgan, no run short of a length outside off, Morgan holds his bat inside the line and it goes through to Wade
Coulter-Nile to Morgan, no run fuller at middle and off, 88mph, pushed firmly back down the pitch
Coulter-Nile to Morgan, 1 run hint of width, cut in the air through the vacant gully area to third man
Coulter-Nile to Ali, no run a bouncer over leg stump, Moeen pulls out of an aggressive stroke
Coulter-Nile to Ali, 3 runs that's a gorgeous piece of timing, punches a back-of-a-length delivery wide of mid-off but it's heading towards one of the long corners on the ground
Coulter-Nile to Morgan, no run done for pace by a ball which slides across outside off
Cummins to Ali, no run plays over the top of a full delivery outside off...91mph
Cummins to Ali, no run good length at off stump, 91mph, pushed firmly to mid-off
Cummins to Ali, no run fuller this time, another drive again finds mid-off
Cummins to Ali, 1 run direct hit! But Moeen's makes it with a dive. He picked out mid-off, again, with a drive but this time opted to sprint off for the run
Cummins to Morgan, no run excellent pressure being built as Morgan drives a full delivery to mid-off
Cummins to Morgan, FOUR runs finds the gap this time, drives through the line and this time opens the face a fraction to place it wide of cover...that whistled off the bat
Marsh to Ali, FOUR runs now Moeen goes over the off side, a flowing drive which he places wide of the point sweeper
Marsh to Ali, no run drags the length back, pushed into the backward-point area
Marsh to Ali, 1 run tight on middle and off, slower at 75mph, pushed into the off side
Marsh to Morgan, no run comes down the pitch then gets beaten on the under edge as he tries to play through the off side...ball travels over the stumps
Marsh to Morgan, FOUR runs short ball at the body, Morgan swivels on a pull which goes very fine to one of the shorter, straight boundaries
Marsh to Morgan, 1 run back of a length outside off, a cutter, chopped down to third man
Maxwell to Morgan, no run round the wicket, touch short but Morgan cracks it straight to cover
Maxwell to Morgan, 1 run slides on, Morgan exposes his stumps as he moves to the leg side but is able to cut to deep point
Maxwell to Ali, 1 run flicked through midwicket
Maxwell to Morgan, 1 run fuller at the stumps, driven down to long-off
Maxwell to Ali, no run fired in at the pads, Moeen goes for a sweep but doesn't make contact and the ball bobbles to short fine leg

Maxwell to Ali, 3 runs drops short this time, Moeen latches on with a pull in front of square...Starc at deep square makes a good diving save, but then makes a bit of a best of trying to get the ball back. The batsmen take a third, and then Morgan has to dive to make his ground
Stoinis to Ali, no run on a length at off stump, 74mph, pushed into the off side
Stoinis to Ali, SIX runs that's a mighty blow! Dragged down short, Moeen is already coming down the pitch and then he pulls it handsomely over deep square leg
Stoinis to Ali, FOUR runs short again, around off stump, sits up nicely and Moeen dismissively bludgeons him through straight midwicket
Stoinis to Ali, 1 run gets this a little fuller, driven down to long-off
Stoinis to Morgan, 1 run another short ball, Morgan's pull is not as convincing as Moeen's earlier in the over, takes a top edge, but lands short of deep square
Stoinis to Ali, 1 run fuller outside off, driven square out to deep point
Maxwell to Ali, 1 run flicked from around off stump down to long-on
Maxwell to Morgan, 1 run uses his feet, Maxwell drags the length back and Morgan can only nudge into the leg side...thought of a second for a moment as Wade chases it
Maxwell to Ali, 1 run sweeps a straight delivery to short fine leg
Maxwell to Morgan, 1 run follows Morgan as he moves to the leg side, the pull comes from high on the bat and lobs down towards long-on
Maxwell to Ali, 1 run width outside off, cut to deep cover
Maxwell to Morgan, 1 run ends up cutting this delivery from well outside leg as he had moved so far to the on side, picks out deep cover
Marsh to Morgan, FOUR runs he sounds the bugle, comes down the pitch and clubs a length delivery over mid-on...not clearly timed, off the bottom of the bat, but easily cleared mid-on
Marsh to Morgan, SIX runs ah, that's sweet! Gee, that made a good sound. Drills through the line of a fuller delivery and sends it perfectly straight down the ground
Marsh to Morgan, 1 run a lot of slower balls from Marsh, this one nudged into the leg side
Marsh to Ali, no run a slower bouncer now, outside off at 72mph, Moeen is through his pull far too early
Marsh to Ali, no run back of a length at off stump, driven from the back foot into the covers
Marsh to Ali, no run another slower short ball, Moeen is defeated again as he tries to swing through the leg side...Marsh recovered well after those boundaries
Coulter-Nile to Morgan, no run short of a length, cramps Morgan for room as he aims to play to the off side
Coulter-Nile to Morgan, 1 run a slower ball down the leg side, paddled out to deep square
Coulter-Nile to Ali, 2 runs pulls a short ball, comes off the splice but falls into space over midwicket and long-on runs around
Coulter-Nile to Ali, FOUR runs fuller on middle and leg and that's sweetly picked up over the leg side, didn't try to hit that one too hard
Coulter-Nile to Ali, FOUR runs gets right across his stumps this time, it's a fuller ball and his wrists come into play as he flicks it wide of short fine-leg. Hands on head for the bowler
Coulter-Nile to Ali, no run outside off, clubbed back to the bowler
Watson to Morgan, 2 runs full outside off, skewed over point as Morgan tries clear the off side...the bat face turned in his hand

Watson to Morgan, SIX runs what a shot! Astonishing power from Morgan, albeit to the shorter boundary, as he comes down the pitch. Watson saw him, dropped it shorter but Morgan was still able to muscle it over long-off with a cross-batted swing
Watson to Morgan, no run driven in the air but short of cover
Watson to Morgan, no run shuffles across his crease, Watson pushes it outside off and Morgan is beaten
Watson to Morgan, 1 run full at the stumps, driven down the ground
Watson to Ali, 2 runs drives a full ball very firmly through the off side, stayed on leg stump so he could free his arms, all along the ground wide of the sweeper
Boyce to Morgan, 1 run drags the first one down a little outside off, pulled to long-on
Boyce to Ali, SIX runs he targets the short boundary, basically just slugs a length delivery straight down the ground
Boyce to Ali, FOUR runs short again, and this time it's pulled with power and placement wide of deep midwicket. Lovely quick footwork and quick hands. Superb fifty off 31 balls
Boyce to Ali, SIX runs that's bigger! Uses his feet and picks up a delivery around leg stump with a free swing of the arms over deep midwicket. Effortless.
Boyce to Ali, 1 run a quicker ball, fired it around leg stump, pushed down the ground
Boyce to Morgan, 1 run full outside off, chopped into the ground off a bottom edge and bobbles to point
Watson to Morgan, SIX runs six more! The charge is well and truly on. Another supreme strike by Morgan as he drives a full delivery well over long on
Watson to Morgan, 2 runs low full toss outside off, driven sweetly through the off side and the sweeper can't stop the second
Watson to Morgan, no run gets a leading edge as he aims to work a delivery off his pads but it loops short of Smith running in from cover
Watson to Morgan, SIX runs into the crowd again! Terrific way to go to fifty off 32 balls...hoicks a short ball over deep square leg even though he was cramped for a little room
Watson to Morgan, SIX runs brilliant strike, hammers through the line of a full ball as Watson tries to mix up his length but it just goes straight back over his head
Watson to Morgan, 1 wide the pressure tells, fired miles outside off stump
Watson to Morgan, 1 run full at the stumps, gets underneath it and chips just short of long-on...22 off the over
Cummins to Morgan, 1 run low full toss outside off, driven in the air but lands short of deep cover
Cummins to Ali, 1 run full at leg stump, flicked out to deep midwicket
Cummins to Morgan, 1 run gets a yorker in which is squeezed to the covers
Cummins to Ali, 1 run another full toss, Moeen gives himself room to the leg side and drives through point...Warner's speed across the ground keeps them to one
Cummins to Morgan, SIX runs these straight boundaries are very short...Morgan manages to larrup a big full toss off somewhere near the bottom of the bat and it lands in the crowd
Cummins to Morgan, SIX runs that's one of the longer boundaries...and it's six again. Cummins drops it short and Morgan pulls emphatically over deep midwicket
Coulter-Nile to Ali, 1 run he goes straight down the ground, too, but clothed a little by Moeen
Coulter-Nile to Morgan, OUT gets underneath this, goes miles into the Cardiff sky and does not quite have the distance this time as Watson settles under it just inside the rope at long on
Coulter-Nile to Ali, no run that's sharp, a short ball at leg stump which beats Moeen over the top edge
Coulter-Nile to Ali, 2 runs fuller this time, heaved through midwicket and places it between two of the deep men
Coulter-Nile to Ali, 1 run short of a length, Moeen moves to the leg side and pulls over midwicket...doesn't quite fine the middle
Coulter-Nile to Buttler, 1 run back of a length, straight, tucked into the leg side...good over from NCL and a good spell
Starc to Buttler, FOUR runs superb placement from Buttler as he lofts a full ball over extra cover, just opened the blade to find the gap
Starc to Buttler, SIX runs and now he clears wide long-on...another full delivery and Buttler switches sides, launching it over the in-field and that didn't even find the middle
Starc to Buttler, 1 wide a wide full toss outside off
Starc to Buttler, OUT finds mid-on...clubs a length delivery and doesn't get elevation or placement. A brief, lively stay for Buttler. Next!
Starc to Billings, no run round the wicket, full outside off, 90mph, driven straight to cover
Starc to Billings, no run well bowled, beaten outside off by a full ball at 91mph
Starc to Billings, no run a fresh air swing from Billings as he charges down the pitch...so he soaks up three dot balls
Cummins to Ali, 1 run full outside off, cracked over the off side to deep cover
Cummins to Billings, 1 run charges down the pitch, beaten for pace by a very sharp delivery above 90mph, goes for a pull which skews into the off side
Cummins to Ali, no run connects sweetly with a drive but it goes straight to cover...some valuable dot balls for Australia

Cummins to Ali, 2 leg byes somehow gets this down to third man, goes right across the crease outside off and aims to work to the leg side then the ball takes the pad...a better throw and he would have been struggling
Cummins to Ali, 1 run full at the stumps, 91mph, driven firmly to deep cover
Cummins to Billings, 1 leg bye done for pace again, nudging 94mph, rattles into the top of his leg as he tries to pull and the leg bye means it keeps the strike which Australia won't mind
Starc to Billings, 1 run round the wicket, full outside leg, Billings gets a leading edge out to deep cover
Starc to Ali, FOUR runs over the wicket, and elegantly sliced away over backward point, it was a full delivery and he allowed the ball to slide off an open face
Starc to Ali, 1 run low full toss, this time he drives out to deep cover so loses the strike
Starc to Billings, OUT a straight, low full toss is driven straight to mid-off...Smith's throw is on target, Starc takes the bails off. Billings struggled today
Starc to Ali, 1 run well bowled, yorker outside off, Moeen can only heave into the leg side
Starc to Stokes, 1 run one ball for Stokes, it's a low full toss which he crunches straight to mid-off who is inside the circle

That's a good finish for Australia - 30 off the last four overs - but still a strong total for England based around two fantastic innings from Moeen Ali and Eoin Morgan. It was a case of the quicker they bowled, the better for Australia. Starc, Cummins and Coulter-Nile very good. The others
We are just about ready for the chase...Warner and Watson to open for Australia. If they win this, it will be their second-highest T20 chase ever. David Willey with the opening over...
Willey to Warner, no run back of a length outside off, takes the toe of the bat towards cover
Willey to Warner, 2 runs gets this through the in field, comes onto the front foot and drives between cover and mid-off
Willey to Warner, no run big appeal for lbw, but that looked high and leg-side...good ball, though, nipped back off a length and Warner just fell across the shot
Willey to Warner, no run flicked from off stump into midwicket
Willey to Warner, 2 runs full delivery, Warner lofts it over the off side but without quite his full power

Willey to Warner, OUT gone! Taken at third man! Curious dismissal, but not entirely dissimilar to a couple of the Test dismissals when he was out pulling. Was a shorter delivery, Warner wanted to play into the leg side and got into a bit of a tangle, the ball took the thick leading ed
Finn to Watson, FOUR runs short of a length outside off, Watson latches on with a thumping front-foot pull through straight midwicket
Finn to Watson, no run good comeback from Finn, fuller outside off and nips away off the seam to beat Watson as he plays away from his body
Finn to Watson, no run a bouncer, over off stump, close to a wide but Finn gets away with it
Finn to Watson, FOUR runs lovely stroke, effortless as he drives a full delivery wide of mid-off...a bit floaty from Finn

Finn to Watson, OUT dragged on! Oh Watto! Would you believe it. A good length ball from Finn which he defended down by his feet. It them bobbles back towards the stumps, Watson tries to kick it away but misses and can only watch as the ball dislodged a bail
Finn to Maxwell, no run
Willey to Smith, 1 run clipped through square leg
Willey to Maxwell, no run defended to the off side
Willey to Maxwell, FOUR runs width outside off and it's hammered through square cover as Maxwell frees his arms

Willey to Maxwell, no run plenty going on here! A good ball from Willey, short of a length, which nips back at Maxwell who fends it towards slip. Smith races up for a single but Maxwell isn't moving and Smith has to sprint back. The throw is wild in any event
Willey to Maxwell, FOUR runs swivels on a pull which goes backward of square...a very well-controlled stroke, not brute force
Willey to Maxwell, 1 run clipped off the pads to deep square
Finn to Maxwell, FOUR runs full and straight, drilled down the ground with plenty of bottom hand...didn't try to over-hit, just slotted it back past the bowler
Finn to Maxwell, no run drags the length back, 84mph, on middle and off, defended

Finn to Maxwell, 1 run goes for a booming drive to a full delivery, gets an inside edge into the pads...starts off for a run, would have been tight with a direct hit, then he gets an overthrow as Stokes pings his shy to deep square
Finn to Smith, FOUR runs short on off stump, Smith gets inside the line and pulls behind square...had some much time
Finn to Smith, 1 run super fielding by Stokes, driven on the up into backward point and he flings himself low to his left to cut off a boundary...almost made it a blinding catch, to
Finn to Maxwell, no run short of a length, Maxwell goes for a pull but just gets taken on the pad
Topley to Smith, no run left arm over, back of a length at off stump, driven to cover
Topley to Smith, no run fuller outside off, 81mph, Smith stays on the back foot and drives square to point
Topley to Smith, FOUR runs just over mid-on! Smith drives a full delivery and manages to evade Willey who had come in a few paces. Was a slower ball out of the back of the hand
Topley to Smith, 1 run gets away with a short ball as Smith flays it to cover who parries it away for a single
Topley to Maxwell, no run a clean piece of work this time from Roy at cover as Smith drives with his bottom hand coming off the bat
Topley to Maxwell, no run can't get through the off side, drives a back-of-a-length delivery to cover...good start from Topley
Finn to Smith, SIX runs fantastic stroke, a glorious straight six by Smith as he lofts a full delivery towards the short boundary
Finn to Smith, 1 run whips this from well outside off to deep square
Finn to Maxwell, no run gives himself room to the leg side and then gets beaten by a very full delivery which he tries to drive
Finn to Maxwell, no run short ball at the body, pulled straight to midwicket...seemed to hurry on a little
Finn to Maxwell, 1 leg bye nips back off a length and takes the thigh pad behind square on the off side
Finn to Smith, no run drives at a full delivery and bottom edges into his boot
Topley to Maxwell, FOUR runs that's a wild mow across the line, gets an inside edge past the stumps to fine leg
Topley to Maxwell, 1 run back of a length outside off, driven to deep cover
Topley to Smith, 1 run close with a direct hit! A slower ball outside off, dropped towards point. Stokes quickly and has an under-arm flick. Very tight, but he missed the stums
Topley to Maxwell, FOUR runs gets this past deep cover, could Hales have done better? Driven square through point. Yes, Hales made a bit of a mess of that
Topley to Maxwell, no run short of a length at middle and leg, worked to midwicket
Topley to Maxwell, FOUR runs that's a sweet pull, Maxwell is up and running, Topley drops it short and it gets dispatched in front of square
Rashid to Smith, no run full outside off, driven firmly to cover who makes a good save
Rashid to Smith, 1 run slow, loopy outside off, Smith drives down to long off
Rashid to Maxwell, 1 run Yorkshire to Yorkshire, straighter delivery which is eased down the ground
Rashid to Smith, 1 run full at the stumps, pushed to long-off...fifty stand in 35 balls
Rashid to Maxwell, 1 run waits for this outside off and cuts to deep cover
Rashid to Smith, 1 run a shorter delivery which slides into Smith who sends it through midwicket with a straight bat
Stokes to Smith, 1 run short of a length at off stump, shovelled round the corner to short fine leg
Stokes to Maxwell, 1 run gets across onto off stump and tucks through midwicket
Stokes to Smith, 1 leg bye aims to flick a back-of-a-length delivery and it takes the thigh pad behind square
Stokes to Maxwell, 1 leg bye tucked off the hip...ah, again no bat involved
Stokes to Smith, FOUR runs excellent placement as he pulls a short ball through square leg...bisects the two men in the deep
Stokes to Smith, 1 run not far off another catch to third man as Smith flashes hard at width outside off, but it goes one bounce to Rashid
Rashid to Smith, SIX runs put down in the crowd as Smith uses his feet then launches Rashid over long-on...wasn't quite to the pitch, but just went through with the stroke
Rashid to Smith, 1 run straight down the ground again, not quite the power this time, and long-off comes around
Rashid to Maxwell, 2 runs on leg stump, goes for the sweep, gets it very fine and Finn is just able to catch up with it
Rashid to Maxwell, 1 run flicks a straight delivery into the leg side
Rashid to Smith, 2 runs dragged down short outside off, Smith fetches it and pulls through midwicket wide of long-on
Rashid to Smith, 1 run driven off the back foot to long-off

Stokes to Smith, 2 runs short again, pulled behind square...good piece of fielding and a strong throw from Finn means Smith has to get the dive out . He's fully airborne, brilliant effort, and he gets home
Stokes to Smith, no run comes down the pitch outside leg stump and has a wild swing at a length delivery
Stokes to Smith, 2 runs another short one, pulled through midwicket but not out of the middle
Stokes to Smith, FOUR runs superb batting, a slower ball outside off, Smith waits a fraction longer for it then drives square through the off side to beat deep point
Stokes to Smith, 1 leg bye short into the body, 88mph, takes Smith's body down by his feet...Maxwell calls him through, Stokes shows his football skills by kicking into the stumps
Stokes to Maxwell, 1 run deft batting this time, short outside off and Maxwell late cuts to third man
Rashid to Maxwell, SIX runs short ball is costly, a freebie to Maxwell as he rocks back and pulls it high into the stands over deep square leg
Rashid to Maxwell, 1 run gets this fuller, on leg stump, calmly pushed down the ground...mature batting
Rashid to Smith, no run full outside off, driven to cover
Rashid to Smith, FOUR runs he's drilled that straight down the ground, more swift footwork and he took it from outside off straight of long-on...a very good fifty from 30 balls
Rashid to Smith, 1 run driven to deep cover
Rashid to Maxwell, 2 runs pushed gently through midwicket and the soft placement gives them the chance to come back for a second
Finn to Smith, 2 runs length outside off, carved through the covers wide of the sweeper

Finn to Smith, 2 runs a rather ungainly heave through the leg side but it's quite effective, almost reaches the boundary but Billings produces an outstanding piece of work as he slides around the boundary
Finn to Smith, SIX runs that's huge! That made the perfect 'crack' off the bat as Smith swung a length delivery into the pavilion at deep square-leg. Blimey, that was big
Finn to Smith, 1 run short of a length, pulled along the ground to deep square
Finn to Maxwell, 1 run blocked from off stump into the covers...more sensible batting
Finn to Smith, 2 runs short outside off, clubbed wide of Morgan at cover and it's another brace

Ali to Maxwell, OUT watch a catch! He's struck first ball. But it's all down to Ben Stokes. It was a short ball, Maxwell fluffed his pull but it was still travelling wide of long on before Stokes ran around, diving to his right and pulled off a blinder
Ali to Smith, 1 run nudged into the leg side
Ali to Marsh, no run on off stump, defended
Ali to Marsh, no run gets across the crease to a slightly shorter ball, takes the pad to the leg side
Ali to Marsh, 1 run worked down the ground to long-on
Ali to Smith, 1 run flicked off the stumps out to deep midwicket...the over England needed
Stokes to Smith, no run back of a length outside off, pushed square to point
Stokes to Smith, FOUR runs dropped short, too much of that from England's quicks today, and Smith slots it away over midwicket with a front-foot pull
Stokes to Smith, 1 run gets this fuller, slugged down the ground to long-on
Stokes to Marsh, no run full at off stump, 88mph, pushed to cover
Stokes to Marsh, 2 runs short of a length, angled into the hip, flicked away between deep square and long leg
Stokes to Marsh, no run full at off stump, driven sweetly off the front foot but straight to mid-off
Topley to Smith, no run full outside off, Smith loses his shape and mistimes back to the bowler
Topley to Smith, 2 runs length outside off, driven almost straight to deep cover but they still manage a second...ah, Billings slipped a little
Topley to Smith, 2 runs a yorker which is squeezed out square through the off side
Topley to Smith, 1 run keeps it full at the stumps, low full toss this time, driven to deep cover
Topley to Marsh, 2 runs fired in at leg stump, flicked through midwicket and more good running brings another couple
Topley to Marsh, 1 run slower ball, dragged down short, Smith swings it to midwicket...good effort from Topley
Willey to Marsh, 1 run full and straight, Marsh swings to the leg side and gets an inside edge to short fine leg
Willey to Smith, FOUR runs brilliant invention from Smith, he moves across his crease and then pulls a short delivery from well outside off behind square on the leg side
Willey to Smith, SIX runs that's even better from Smith, this time he stays on leg stump and drives it over deep cover into the stands...two wonderful pieces of batting
Willey to Smith, no run a slower bouncer, Smith swings through his shot and gets beaten
Willey to Smith, 1 run back of a length, sliced in the air over cover to the sweeper
Willey to Marsh, 1 run swung from outside off to deep midwicket
Topley to Marsh, FOUR runs oh dear, that's a horrid misfield...Marsh drives firmly to long-off and Moeen lets it through his legs. His first mistake of the day
Topley to Marsh, 1 run clubbed to long-on
Topley to Smith, 1 run a slightly more ungainly pull this time down to long-on
Topley to Stoinis, 1 run round the wicket, full at off stump, calmly pushed to long-on
Topley to Smith, 1 run yorker to finish with, down to long-off
Willey to Smith, 1 run round the wicket, back of a length, connects well with a swing through midwicket but straight to the man in the deep
Willey to Stoinis, 1 run neatly played, gets inside the line and tucks it off his pads to long leg

Willey to Smith, OUT he's gone! Ten short of a hundred. Smith got too far underneath this as he aimed to clear deep midwicket. The ball went high, came off the bottom of the bat and his hand came off the handle...Billings takes the vital catch
Willey to Stoinis, FOUR runs places it between two men! Another short ball, Stoinis pulls strongly, in the air for most of the way and neither deep square or midwicket can quite get around
Willey to Stoinis, 1 leg bye fuller this time, at the stumps, an aborted appeal for lbw...was going down
Willey to Wade, 1 run back over the wicket, full and straight, driven to long-off

Stokes to Wade, 1 run, OUT mix-up! A length ball is swung to long-off, Wade turned and, head down, wanted the second for Stoinis didn't fancy it and left his team-mate stranded. The throw was decent and Stokes whipped off the bails
Stokes to Stoinis, no run well bowled! A yorker outside off, swing and a miss from Stoinis as he lifts his head on the shot
Stokes to Stoinis, 1 wide oh dear, that's not good, a slower ball down the leg side...extra run, extra ball
Stokes to Stoinis, 1 run full and straight, driven straight to long-off, they won't get two here

Stokes to Stoinis, 1 run, OUT another run out! England brilliant in this last over. Full at leg stump, drilled down to long on. They had to gamble on the second run but the return was quick and flat, Stokes was by the stumps and completes his second run out of the over
Stokes to Stoinis, 2 runs heaved into the leg side, it's not enough
That just about wraps things up for today, thanks for joining us and see you for the first ODI on Thursday. For now, though, it's goodbye.

England win by five runs and they did exceptionally well to close out that game after Smith and Maxwell had put Australia in a strong position. Willey, Stokes and Topley, on debut, produced some telling overs at the death while Morgan marshalled his team expertly. Some calm fielding, too, w
England won by 5 runs
Player of the match is Moeen Ali, ENG
